main event: A civilian reported a sighting of a small grey-like object with red and white flashing lights over Proctor, Minnesota on August 9, 1965.
interesting points: The object was reported to be stationary before slowly moving to the northwest., The sighting duration was not specified, but it was still in sight at the time of the report., The object changed colors as it was observed by two military officers., The Air Force evaluated this case as unidentified., Witnesses included a civilian and two military officers.
sighted object: small grey-like object with red and white flashing lights
